<statement>
<p>Solve the equation: <m>\displaystyle{18}{\left({10}^{{-{9}{x}}}\right)}-{4}={0}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=</m><fillin characters="6" /> </p>
<p>Round to 3 decimal places.</p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>0.073</li></ul></p><p><m>\displaystyle{18}{\left({10}^{{-{9}{x}}}\right)}-{4}={0}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{18}{\left({10}^{{-{9}{x}}}\right)}=-{4}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{10}^{{-{9}{x}}}=-\frac{{4}}{{18}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{9}{x}={\log{{\left(-\frac{{4}}{{18}}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{\log{{\left(-\frac{{4}}{{18}}\right)}}}}{{-{{9}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}\approx{0.073}</m></p>
</solution>
</myopenmath>

